# No silent scalar coercion on a REASSIGNMENT (not just a typed decl). `x` is int; a
# later `x = 2.5` silently truncated the float to 2 in tychoc0 while tychoc rejects.
# Both compilers must reject. (UB-6 completion at the SAssign position.)
fn main():
    x : int = 7
    x = 2.5
    println(str(x))
